  "Changing the equation to a graph": "",
  "Rewriting an equation to isolate a different variable": "",
  "Removing all operations": "",
  "Adding new variables to the equation": "",
  "Rearranging an equation means using algebraic operations to rewrite it so a different variable is isolated on one side.": "",
  "What does 'subject of a formula' mean?": "",
  "The largest variable in the formula": "",
  "The variable that is isolated on one side of the formula": "",
  "The variable that equals zero": "",
  "The first variable alphabetically": "",
