  "A scientist uses the formula d = rt to calculate distance. She knows a car traveled 240 miles in 4 hours. She rearranges to find the rate. What formula does she use and what is r?": "",
  "r = d/t; r = 60 mph": "",
  "r = d - t; r = 236 mph": "",
  "r = dt; r = 960 mph": "",
  "r = t/d; r = 0.017 mph": "",
  "Rearrange d = rt to r = d/t. Substitute: r = 240/4 = 60 mph.": "",
  "A homeowner wants to know the width of a rectangular room. The perimeter is 56 feet and the length is 18 feet. Using P = 2l + 2w, solve for w and find its value.": "",
  "w = 2P - l; w = 94 feet": "",
  "w = (P - 2l)/2; w = 10 feet": "",
  "w = P/2; w = 28 feet": "",
  "w = P - l; w = 38 feet": "",
  "w = (P - 2l)/2 = (56 - 36)/2 = 20/2 = 10 feet.": "",
  "A nurse converts a patient's temperature from Celsius to Fahrenheit using F = (9/5)C + 32. If the patient's temperature is 38°C, what is it in Fahrenheit?": "",
  "98.6°F": "",
  "100.4°F": "",
  "96.8°F": "",
  "102.2°F": "",
  "F = (9/5)(38) + 32 = 68.4 + 32 = 100.4°F.": "",
  "An architect uses A = (1/2)bh to find the area of a triangular window. The area must be 24 square feet and the base is 8 feet. Solve for h and find the height.": "",
  "h = A/b; h = 3 feet": "",
  "h = 2b/A; h = 0.67 feet": "",
  "h = Ab/2; h = 96 feet": "",
  "h = 2A/b; h = 6 feet": "",
  "h = 2A/b = 2(24)/8 = 48/8 = 6 feet.": "",
  "A student needs to find the original price of an item that was discounted 20%. The sale price was $48. Using S = P(1 - r), solve for P.": "",
  "P = S + r; P = $48.20": "",
  "P = S/(1 - r); P = $60": "",
  "P = S/r; P = $240": "",
  "P = S(1 - r); P = $38.40": "",
  "P = S/(1 - r) = 48/(1 - 0.20) = 48/0.80 = $60.": "",
  "A physics student uses v = u + at to study motion. A car accelerates from 10 m/s to 30 m/s in 5 seconds. Solve for a and find the acceleration.": "",
  "a = v + u + t; a = 45 m/s²": "",
  "a = vt - u; a = 140 m/s²": "",
  "a = (v + u)/t; a = 8 m/s²": "",
  "a = (v - u)/t; a = 4 m/s²": "",
  "a = (v - u)/t = (30 - 10)/5 = 20/5 = 4 m/s².": "",
  "A baker uses a recipe that relates cups of flour (f), sugar (s), and butter (b) as f = 2s + b. If she has 5 cups of flour and 1 cup of butter, how many cups of sugar can she use?": "",
  "s = f - b; s = 4 cups": "",
  "s = (f + b)/2; s = 3 cups": "",
  "s = 2f - b; s = 9 cups": "",
  "s = (f - b)/2; s = 2 cups": "",
  "Solve for s: f - b = 2s, so s = (f - b)/2 = (5 - 1)/2 = 4/2 = 2 cups.": "",
  "A pool manager uses V = lwh to calculate the volume of a rectangular pool. The pool holds 4,800 cubic feet, is 40 feet long and 20 feet wide. Solve for h to find the depth.": "",
  "h = V/(lw); h = 6 feet": "",
  "h = lw/V; h = 0.17 feet": "",
  "h = Vlw; h = 3,840,000 feet": "",
  "h = V - lw; h = 4,000 feet": "",
  "h = V/(lw) = 4800/(40 × 20) = 4800/800 = 6 feet.": "",
